00:44:28.949 --> 00:44:32.032
Rome,
so you have more than 1,000

00:44:32.032 --> 00:44:35.612
years where sort of no
intellectual progress with

00:44:35.612 --> 00:44:37.849
respect to reality is made.
 

00:44:37.849 --> 00:44:43.090
Then things all of a sudden
start to change and we're going

00:44:43.090 --> 00:44:45.349
to talk about that now.
 

00:44:45.349 --> 00:44:51.144
Within 200 years the death rate
falls dramatically and so has

00:44:51.144 --> 00:44:54.719
the birth rate--falls
dramatically.

00:44:54.719 --> 00:44:58.679
These changes are sort of the
centerpiece of what,

00:44:58.679 --> 00:45:00.246
of course in
demography--historical

00:45:00.246 --> 00:45:02.230
demography anybody that usually
studies--

00:45:02.230 --> 00:45:04.780
is called the demographic
transition: the fall in the

00:45:04.780 --> 00:45:06.940
death rate and the fall in the
birth rate.

00:45:06.940 --> 00:45:10.954
You'll hear this many times
because it's so basic that in

00:45:10.954 --> 00:45:14.036
these periods,
old periods the birth rate is

00:45:14.036 --> 00:45:17.119
very high, the death rate is
very high.

00:45:17.119 --> 00:45:23.175
They're about equal so
population basically grows not

00:45:23.175 --> 00:45:26.670
at all or very,
very slowly.

00:45:26.670 --> 00:45:29.599
What we're going to talk about
now in turn is first,

00:45:29.599 --> 00:45:34.242
the fall in the death rate,
and the second,

00:45:34.242 --> 00:45:40.545
then the fall in the birth
rate, and then theories that we

00:45:40.545 --> 00:45:47.398
have to explain these enormous
changes in what it means to be a

00:45:47.398 --> 00:45:49.389
human being.
 

00:45:49.389 --> 00:45:53.889
What happened--we don't know
the causes or we have many,

00:45:53.889 --> 00:45:55.199
many theories.
 

00:45:55.199 --> 00:45:57.519
Maybe we many,
many times know what the causes

00:45:57.519 --> 00:45:57.829
are.
 

00:45:57.829 --> 00:46:03.880
One of the standard textbooks
of European History says--

00:46:03.880 --> 00:46:08.813
this is going back to the wars
of religion which is just before

00:46:08.813 --> 00:46:13.110
all these changes started
happening before Galileo,

00:46:13.110 --> 00:46:16.431
for instance--"One thing
was clear, 130 years of

00:46:16.431 --> 00:46:20.009
senseless bloodletting in the
name of religion inevitably

00:46:20.009 --> 00:46:23.969
sparked off a reaction in the
minds of intelligent people.

00:46:23.969 --> 00:46:28.534
The wars of religion offered
fertile soil for the fragile

00:46:28.534 --> 00:46:30.980
seeds of reason and science.
 

00:46:30.980 --> 00:46:35.235
People began to realize that
religiosity was hostile to

00:46:35.235 --> 00:46:36.889
civilization."
 

00:46:36.889 --> 00:46:39.748
Europeans say,
because of this period of sort

00:46:39.748 --> 00:46:43.255
of utter irrationality,
that the bad results of it were

00:46:43.255 --> 00:46:45.789
so immediately obvious to
everyone.

00:46:45.789 --> 00:46:49.041
Everyone was getting scared of
getting killed by the people in

00:46:49.041 --> 00:46:51.920
the neighboring town who were of
the other religion;

00:46:51.920 --> 00:46:57.313
they rejected all that and were
ready for some sort of a

00:46:57.313 --> 00:47:00.650
rational attitude toward things.
 

00:47:00.650 --> 00:47:08.380
The results of that we can see
were really quite dramatic.

00:47:08.380 --> 00:47:13.695
Here is what we can reconstruct
of life expectancy and going

00:47:13.695 --> 00:47:18.739
back 8,000 years ago where the
records are very poor,

00:47:18.739 --> 00:47:20.989
but it certainly wasn't much
better than this.

00:47:20.989 --> 00:47:25.353
And there was wavering,
and probably some slow increase

00:47:25.353 --> 00:47:27.050
in life expectancy.
 

00:47:27.050 --> 00:47:31.501
This, just above 20 years of
life expectancy is what I showed

00:47:31.501 --> 00:47:35.878
you in the graph of Cisalpine
Gaul from Roman Times and what

00:47:35.878 --> 00:47:40.402
I've told you is true of Europe
during these hundreds of years

00:47:40.402 --> 00:47:43.000
that I've been talking about.
 

00:47:43.000 --> 00:47:45.730
That stays more or less the
same with perhaps some

00:47:45.730 --> 00:47:46.510
improvement.
 

00:47:46.510 --> 00:47:49.251
It doesn't matter whether
you're looking at France-the

00:47:49.251 --> 00:47:52.199
dotted line, or you're looking
at China-the solid line.

00:47:52.199 --> 00:47:57.188
As far as we can tell they're
pretty much the same until

00:47:57.188 --> 00:48:01.083
around 1700,
all of a sudden something

00:48:01.083 --> 00:48:05.849
majorly changes and the life
expectancy goes--

00:48:05.849 --> 00:48:07.449
starts going sky high.
 

00:48:07.449 --> 00:48:10.579
We're talking about not just
one of many,

00:48:10.579 --> 00:48:13.943
many things that happened in
history that you can take all

00:48:13.943 --> 00:48:17.735
kinds of history courses about,
but in terms of what it means

00:48:17.735 --> 00:48:22.157
to be a human,
you finally can stay alive

00:48:22.157 --> 00:48:25.860
beyond the age of 20 or 25.
 

00:48:25.860 --> 00:48:31.976
That is such a tremendous
change in life that there's

00:48:31.976 --> 00:48:35.268
nothing else as important.
 

00:48:35.268 --> 00:48:39.686
Of course a large part of this,
to reinforce this,

00:48:39.686 --> 00:48:41.760
was infant mortality.
 

00:48:41.760 --> 00:48:46.769
Look what happens,
back here it's going up and

00:48:46.769 --> 00:48:50.889
down like crazy and it's very
high.

00:48:50.889 --> 00:48:55.764
This a quarter of children and
this is European data,

00:48:55.764 --> 00:49:00.920
so this is about a fifth to a
quarter of children die as

00:49:00.920 --> 00:49:04.389
children and it's out of
control.

00:49:04.389 --> 00:49:07.934
You can see that the epidemics
come through and then times get

00:49:07.934 --> 00:49:10.432
good, and then something else
comes through,

00:49:10.432 --> 00:49:12.989
and so it's very variable and
very high.

00:49:12.989 --> 00:49:18.065
Then it starts swooping
downward, and not only does it

00:49:18.065 --> 00:49:22.871
come down but it evens out,
that we start getting control,

00:49:22.871 --> 00:49:26.800
not only over the overall level
but all the things which cause

00:49:26.800 --> 00:49:28.539
these wild swings in it.
 

00:49:28.539 --> 00:49:35.780
Again, an amazing change in
what it means to be human.

00:49:35.780 --> 00:49:39.050
Well what is this date where
things start happening?

00:49:39.050 --> 00:49:42.454
1770s we're into the
Enlightenment and you all have

00:49:42.454 --> 00:49:45.588
probably, at least in your high
school history,

00:49:45.588 --> 00:49:48.039
have heard of the
Enlightenment.

00:49:48.039 --> 00:49:53.137
And that is the big opening out
in Europe of rational discourse

00:49:53.137 --> 00:49:57.331
on almost everything,
and everything from science to

00:49:57.331 --> 00:49:58.400
politics.
 

00:49:58.400 --> 00:50:02.485
Disease, for instance,
was considered divine

00:50:02.485 --> 00:50:07.998
punishment upon mankind for
their sins, that's a quote from

00:50:07.998 --> 00:50:09.329
somewhere.
 

00:50:09.329 --> 00:50:13.030
Medical research was considered
sacrilegious.

00:50:13.030 --> 00:50:15.847
Dissection of cadavers what
objected to because "If you

00:50:15.847 --> 00:50:18.523
cut the bodies into pieces
what's going to happen to them

00:50:18.523 --> 00:50:20.530
at the time of the
resurrection?"

00:50:20.530 --> 00:50:24.947
There are all kinds of reasons
that you shouldn't do anything

00:50:24.947 --> 00:50:28.922
to get even the most basic
knowledge of what's inside a

00:50:28.922 --> 00:50:33.340
human body and without that you
can't make any progress.

00:50:33.340 --> 00:50:38.398
The major, major event in the
enlightenment is Newton's

00:50:38.398 --> 00:50:40.179
Principia.
 

00:50:40.179 --> 00:50:43.860
Newton's discussion of
something that sounds rather

00:50:43.860 --> 00:50:44.670
abstract.
 

00:50:44.670 --> 00:50:47.659
What he was worried about was
how the bodies go around in

00:50:47.659 --> 00:50:48.139
heaven.
 

00:50:48.139 --> 00:50:50.750
That's what everyone was trying
to figure out.

00:50:50.750 --> 00:50:54.925
You may remember Copernicus had
already said that things didn't

00:50:54.925 --> 00:50:58.695
go around the earth but they
went around the sun that was

00:50:58.695 --> 00:50:59.369
older.
 

00:50:59.369 --> 00:51:01.668
Keppler had gotten the
mathematics right,

00:51:01.668 --> 00:51:04.541
so they went around not in
circles but in ellipses,

00:51:04.541 --> 00:51:07.070
but nobody had any explanation
for this.

00:51:07.070 --> 00:51:10.634
It was a simple theory;
it was great regularity,

00:51:10.634 --> 00:51:13.018
but no one had any idea why.
 

00:51:13.018 --> 00:51:17.601
Newton's gravitation was what
made it rational in the sense of

00:51:17.601 --> 00:51:22.034
understanding that it was just a
simple force of gravity and

00:51:22.034 --> 00:51:25.039
people don't always understand
the--

00:51:25.039 --> 00:51:29.489
you know the story of the apple
dropping on his head?

00:51:29.489 --> 00:51:33.409
The story is that gave him the
idea of gravitation.

00:51:33.409 --> 00:51:37.246
Apparently--(1) the story is
probably apocryphal totally but

00:51:37.246 --> 00:51:41.083
the import is what everyone was
trying to figure out was the

00:51:41.083 --> 00:51:42.449
heavenly motions.
 

00:51:42.449 --> 00:51:44.737
The moon around the earth,
the earth around the sun,

00:51:44.737 --> 00:51:46.980
the planets around all of these
sorts of things.

00:51:46.980 --> 00:51:51.364
He goes to sleep under the tree
and the apple falls on his head

00:51:51.364 --> 00:51:55.887
and he wakes up and he realizes,
'oh my God the apple fell on my

00:51:55.887 --> 00:51:59.914
head for the same reason that
the moon is held in orbit around

00:51:59.914 --> 00:52:00.840
the earth.'
 

00:52:00.840 --> 00:52:03.170
As you know if there was no
gravity the moon would just--

00:52:03.170 --> 00:52:04.976
here's the earth,
the moon goes around,

00:52:04.976 --> 00:52:07.639
you shut off gravity the moon
goes off in a straight line

00:52:07.639 --> 00:52:08.210
forever.
 

00:52:08.210 --> 00:52:10.512
That was kind of understood
already by Galileo,

00:52:10.512 --> 00:52:13.418
that things in motion will go
in a straight line unless you

00:52:13.418 --> 00:52:14.670
pull them in somehow.
 

00:52:14.670 --> 00:52:17.461
They knew that the earth--the
moon was constantly falling

00:52:17.461 --> 00:52:18.409
toward the earth.
 

00:52:18.409 --> 00:52:20.420
The earth was constantly
falling toward the sun;

00:52:20.420 --> 00:52:22.849
all the planets were constantly
falling towards the sun.

00:52:22.849 --> 00:52:25.427
That was understood,
and they knew that apples fell

00:52:25.427 --> 00:52:28.518
to the earth but they didn't put
the two of them together.

00:52:28.518 --> 00:52:31.521
The great insight of Newton
apparently was realizing that

00:52:31.521 --> 00:52:34.469
this thing on earth that we
could observe and measure on

00:52:34.469 --> 00:52:37.753
earth,
was the same reason that the

00:52:37.753 --> 00:52:42.056
heavens worked,
and this was sort of a

00:52:42.056 --> 00:52:49.331
bombshell that led to the whole
theory of celestial mechanics

00:52:49.331 --> 00:52:56.001
and gravitation and all of
Western science really starts

00:52:56.001 --> 00:52:57.820
from this.
 

00:52:57.820 --> 00:53:01.822
Within 25 years--and people
were--Newton was lionized during

00:53:01.822 --> 00:53:02.840
his lifetime.
 

00:53:02.840 --> 00:53:08.119
It was realized what a
tremendous achievement this was,

00:53:08.119 --> 00:53:12.016
and the relationship to this is
not only the scientific

00:53:12.016 --> 00:53:16.275
achievement that the planets
orbited by the same force which

00:53:16.275 --> 00:53:19.773
drops an apple,
but it was previously believed

00:53:19.773 --> 00:53:23.536
that yes well events on earth
might work by some sort of

00:53:23.536 --> 00:53:26.480
physical laws,
you had Galileo working on

00:53:26.480 --> 00:53:29.768
that, but heaven was ruled by
supernatural laws,

00:53:29.768 --> 00:53:31.969
and now Newton's great insight
was,

00:53:31.969 --> 00:53:33.619
no they're the same laws.
 

00:53:33.619 --> 00:53:36.150
That there's nothing special or
different about the heavens.

00:53:36.150 --> 00:53:41.210
That they work by exactly the
same laws as stones and apples

00:53:41.210 --> 00:53:42.840
falling on earth.
 

00:53:42.840 --> 00:53:46.606
This was really a tremendous
impetus to realize the power of

00:53:46.606 --> 00:53:50.311
rationality and so within 25
years the whole attitude about

00:53:50.311 --> 00:53:52.610
everything changes tremendously.
 

00:53:52.610 --> 00:53:57.681
As the bubonic plague receded,
for reasons we don't know,

00:53:57.681 --> 00:54:02.842
that I showed you that data,
then smallpox starts becoming

00:54:02.842 --> 00:54:07.489
the leading cause of death;
one replacing the other.

00:54:07.489 --> 00:54:10.809
As opposed to what had gone on
before,

00:54:10.809 --> 00:54:12.900
which was supernatural ideas
about it,

00:54:12.900 --> 00:54:16.699
in the 1710s very shortly after
Newton,

00:54:16.699 --> 00:54:18.880
The Royal Scientific Society
again started,

00:54:18.880 --> 00:54:22.179
at this same time,
began a search program,

00:54:22.179 --> 00:54:25.670
research program to gather
information from any place in

00:54:25.670 --> 00:54:29.289
the world on how smallpox could
be controlled or cured.

00:54:29.289 --> 00:54:32.706
Just a new kind of way of
dealing with disease that just

00:54:32.706 --> 00:54:36.000
hadn't been seen before,
and so what did they find?

00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:39.096
They found that,
in Turkey, that they were

00:54:39.096 --> 00:54:42.344
inoculating people,
and what inoculation is,

00:54:42.344 --> 00:54:46.800
the early form--they take
someone that has the disease;

00:54:46.800 --> 00:54:50.969
they take pus from the
disease--what is pus?

00:54:50.969 --> 00:54:54.784
It's white blood cells that
have eaten the virus or

00:54:54.784 --> 00:54:57.079
bacteria,
depending on whether it's

00:54:57.079 --> 00:54:59.929
plague or smallpox,
and have engulfed it and they

00:54:59.929 --> 00:55:02.599
kill the bacteria or virus,
the pathogen.

00:55:02.599 --> 00:55:05.570
You have a dead pathogen but
it's molecules are still there

00:55:05.570 --> 00:55:09.253
and so you can take the pus,
inject it, just cut the skin,

00:55:09.253 --> 00:55:12.557
put it on a person,
and hopefully they're not

00:55:12.557 --> 00:55:16.280
exposed to anymore of the live
virus but the dead--

00:55:16.280 --> 00:55:20.559
presumably the white blood
cells have killed the virus,

00:55:20.559 --> 00:55:25.545
and you just get their
molecules and that induces an

00:55:25.545 --> 00:55:31.018
immune reaction and you become
immune to this disease.

00:55:31.018 --> 00:55:34.976
Local governments started--I'll
tell you more about smallpox in

00:55:34.976 --> 00:55:36.380
a couple of minutes.
 

00:55:36.380 --> 00:55:42.867
In 1750s, again this very early
time, local regulations for

00:55:42.867 --> 00:55:47.119
sewage disposal are getting
started.

00:55:47.119 --> 00:55:51.465
In the 1790s the rich start
using water closets which are

00:55:51.465 --> 00:55:53.250
toilets of some sort.
 

00:55:53.250 --> 00:55:58.076
Not only do they introduce
vaccination, but 1796 they try

00:55:58.076 --> 00:55:59.800
to make it better.
 

00:55:59.800 --> 00:56:02.768
They don't just say,
oh this works by some magic,

00:56:02.768 --> 00:56:05.130
they try to figure out what it
makes it better,

00:56:05.130 --> 00:56:08.628
and Jenner discovers
vaccination, which is instead of

00:56:08.628 --> 00:56:11.590
using pus from a person who had
smallpox--

00:56:11.590 --> 00:56:15.974
there's a very closely related
disease called cowpox which the

00:56:15.974 --> 00:56:19.094
cow maids--
the milk maids get very

00:56:19.094 --> 00:56:21.070
frequently,
and it was noticed,

00:56:21.070 --> 00:56:22.980
because they're now observing
all these things,

00:56:22.980 --> 00:56:25.909
that these women would get sick
but most of them would recover.

00:56:25.909 --> 00:56:29.407
This was a not a lethal
disease, so instead of taking

00:56:29.407 --> 00:56:34.646
the actual smallpox virus,
which vaccination--the early

00:56:34.646 --> 00:56:37.596
inoculation--
did not always work and you

00:56:37.596 --> 00:56:39.630
sometimes did catch the disease
and died.

00:56:39.630 --> 00:56:43.081
Taking it from cowpox rather
than smallpox was less

00:56:43.081 --> 00:56:45.952
dangerous,
but since the viruses are

00:56:45.952 --> 00:56:50.612
closely related to each other a
lot of the molecules are the

00:56:50.612 --> 00:56:57.081
same and you get--
from cowpox you get immunity to

00:56:57.081 --> 00:57:04.690
smallpox and so these diseases
start going down.

00:57:04.690 --> 00:57:09.902
Not only in health but it
starts the industrial

00:57:09.902 --> 00:57:15.682
revolution, in 1711 James
Newcomen invents the steam

00:57:15.682 --> 00:57:16.929
engine.
 

00:57:16.929 --> 00:57:19.981
It's a very,
very inefficient steam engine,

00:57:19.981 --> 00:57:23.762
and it's used only where you
had--can have a very big

00:57:23.762 --> 00:57:27.760
placement and it's used to pump
water out of mines.

00:57:27.760 --> 00:57:32.134
Coal is becoming important for
England to fuel the industrial

00:57:32.134 --> 00:57:35.851
revolution, and you have mines
that are underground,

00:57:35.851 --> 00:57:38.039
and water seeps into them.
 

00:57:38.039 --> 00:57:41.204
You've got to suck out the
water, so how do you pump it

00:57:41.204 --> 00:57:43.550
out, well he invents the steam
engine.

00:57:43.550 --> 00:57:47.289
Then James Watt figures
out--looks at it more

00:57:47.289 --> 00:57:49.797
scientifically,
more rationally,

00:57:49.797 --> 00:57:52.978
and again just like inoculation
being supplanted with

00:57:52.978 --> 00:57:55.179
vaccination they start
improving.

00:57:55.179 --> 00:57:57.293
It's not just that something
works and our ancestors did it

00:57:57.293 --> 00:57:58.860
this way and we don't know why
it works,

00:57:58.860 --> 00:58:00.916
we don't why care it works,
we do it the same way our

00:58:00.916 --> 00:58:01.550
ancestors did.
 

00:58:01.550 --> 00:58:04.860
No they keep thinking about
what they're looking at,

00:58:04.860 --> 00:58:08.570
what they're working on,
and he improves it and in this

00:58:08.570 --> 00:58:12.449
case what James Watt did is,
after the steam comes out,

00:58:12.449 --> 00:58:16.485
he had a condenser to condense
the steam so drop the pressure

00:58:16.485 --> 00:58:19.110
on one side of the piston going
out.

00:58:19.110 --> 00:58:22.030
Just by taking the condenser
instead of--

00:58:22.030 --> 00:58:25.114
letting--having a way of
cooling the steam really

00:58:25.114 --> 00:58:28.650
improves the efficiency of a
steam engine and now with a

00:58:28.650 --> 00:58:32.378
greater efficiency you can make
a smaller steam engine that

00:58:32.378 --> 00:58:35.931
works just as well,
and you can put it on wheels

00:58:35.931 --> 00:58:39.291
and you start getting the
railroad and all kinds of

00:58:39.291 --> 00:58:42.719
smaller factories can start
using steam engines.

00:58:42.719 --> 00:58:48.411
In politics,
this idea is also terribly

00:58:48.411 --> 00:58:50.210
important.
 

00:58:50.210 --> 00:58:55.380
The previous idea was that of a
hierarchical system with God

00:58:55.380 --> 00:59:00.061
appointing kings being--
ruling over nobility and then

00:59:00.061 --> 00:59:03.289
everyone else must obey up this
chain.

00:59:03.289 --> 00:59:05.989
Well what is Newton's idea?
 

00:59:05.989 --> 00:59:09.739
That everything obeys the same
law: gravity.

00:59:09.739 --> 00:59:13.840
That the sun attracts the earth;
the earth attracts the sun,

00:59:13.840 --> 00:59:14.860
equally and opposite.
 

00:59:14.860 --> 00:59:16.199
There's no difference.
 

00:59:16.199 --> 00:59:18.592
The sun does not rule the
universe, it's not better then

00:59:18.592 --> 00:59:20.679
the earth, it works by exactly
the same rules.

00:59:20.679 --> 00:59:23.099
The sun and the earth,
the earth and the moon,

00:59:23.099 --> 00:59:27.101
everything acts by the same
rules, there is no need for some

00:59:27.101 --> 00:59:30.630
sort of central sentient
coordinator of all this,

00:59:30.630 --> 00:59:34.659
but each individual planet,
each individual body,

00:59:34.659 --> 00:59:38.699
all bodies, apples,
working by their own laws,

00:59:38.699 --> 00:59:41.931
by the same laws as everyone
else the universe works

00:59:41.931 --> 00:59:42.820
beautifully.
 

00:59:42.820 --> 00:59:45.059
In fact it works as it does it
work.

00:59:45.059 --> 00:59:49.657
This idea is very consciously
taken over into politics and the

00:59:49.657 --> 00:59:53.266
idea of democracy,
again changes that each person

00:59:53.266 --> 00:59:57.164
acting under his own desires,
his own self interest,

00:59:57.164 --> 01:00:01.742
his own morality can,
by interacting in the same way

01:00:01.742 --> 01:00:04.916
the planets do,
can come out with a system that

01:00:04.916 --> 01:00:05.289
works.
 

01:00:05.289 --> 01:00:10.018
The original theorists of
democracy were very conscious of

01:00:10.018 --> 01:00:14.666
this shift in the way they
looked at the way the universe

01:00:14.666 --> 01:00:17.820
worked and very conscious of
its--

01:00:17.820 --> 01:00:20.400
their debt to Newton on that.
 

01:00:20.400 --> 01:00:24.451
In economics,
how many of you are economics

01:00:24.451 --> 01:00:25.320
majors?
 

01:00:25.320 --> 01:00:27.070
The bust has really taken
effect;

01:00:27.070 --> 01:00:29.670
we used to have lots of
economic majors.

01:00:29.670 --> 01:00:32.289
What is Adam Smith's idea?
 

01:00:32.289 --> 01:00:36.639
The basis of modern economics
is Adam Smith's--

01:00:36.639 --> 01:00:39.827
that no you don't need a
Mercantilist government to

01:00:39.827 --> 01:00:43.025
control everything,
that if each person acts in

01:00:43.025 --> 01:00:46.619
their own self interest by their
own internal rules,

01:00:46.619 --> 01:00:51.641
then the economy will work just
wonderfully and be more

01:00:51.641 --> 01:00:52.849
productive.
 

01:00:52.849 --> 01:00:55.780
Freedom of religion is again
the same thing,

01:00:55.780 --> 01:00:59.155
freedom of conscience,
it's a similar kind of idea

01:00:59.155 --> 01:01:05.815
that each person has its own--
has his own way of working

01:01:05.815 --> 01:01:15.072
things out and that does not
destroy the harmony of the

01:01:15.072 --> 01:01:17.130
universe.
 

01:01:17.130 --> 01:01:24.994
We see that this rationality
changes everything about the way

01:01:24.994 --> 01:01:26.829
humans live.
 

01:01:26.829 --> 01:01:30.320
One of its most important
effects is demography.

01:01:30.320 --> 01:01:34.552
That the population stops dying
and can start increasing,

01:01:34.552 --> 01:01:37.199
and this is exactly what
happens.

01:01:37.199 --> 01:01:41.326
As all this rational attitude
toward death and toward disease

01:01:41.326 --> 01:01:44.047
starts taking hold,
the death rate falls

01:01:44.047 --> 01:01:47.905
tremendously as I've shown you,
the life expectancy goes up,

01:01:47.905 --> 01:01:51.460
infant mortality goes down,
and population starts

01:01:51.460 --> 01:01:53.389
increasing tremendously.
 

01:01:53.389 --> 01:01:55.583
Most people,
at that time,

01:01:55.583 --> 01:02:00.413
believed that a big population
was a wonderful thing and

01:02:00.413 --> 01:02:03.750
they're very optimistic about
it,

01:02:03.750 --> 01:02:07.090
and one of the standard ways of
judging a government,

01:02:07.090 --> 01:02:08.590
when you saw a country that had
a lot of people in it,

01:02:08.590 --> 01:02:11.309
well obviously the government
was doing something right.

01:02:11.309 --> 01:02:15.032
The king at that time was doing
something right because people

01:02:15.032 --> 01:02:16.619
were able to stay alive.
 

01:02:16.619 --> 01:02:20.594
If you saw a country with a low
population, well something was

01:02:20.594 --> 01:02:23.592
wrong, and that was not
necessarily an improper

01:02:23.592 --> 01:02:24.440
attitude.
 

01:02:24.440 --> 01:02:27.463
Up until Malthus,
with some exceptions,

01:02:27.463 --> 01:02:31.523
it was generally the idea that
there was no limit to

01:02:31.523 --> 01:02:36.059
population, that the more the
population the merrier.

01:02:36.059 --> 01:02:44.043
Malthus came along and said,
'hmm there is a problem with

01:02:44.043 --> 01:02:52.596
population,' and he had been
watching--he collected very good

01:02:52.596 --> 01:02:53.880
data.
 

01:02:53.880 --> 01:02:56.320
You read his stuff,
it's really wonderful to read

01:02:56.320 --> 01:02:59.577
because it's extremely modern in
that he tells you the data he is

01:02:59.577 --> 01:03:01.190
collecting;
he analyzes it;

01:03:01.190 --> 01:03:03.911
he tells you what he--what's
wrong with the data,

01:03:03.911 --> 01:03:07.371
why he believes it to a certain
extent but not beyond that and

01:03:07.371 --> 01:03:09.130
all things about the data.
 

01:03:09.130 --> 01:03:15.117
Very--he's writing is like 1798
but it reads like a modern PhD

01:03:15.117 --> 01:03:17.179
thesis, just about.
 

01:03:17.179 --> 01:03:22.309
His knowledge was the
following, and it's very simple

01:03:22.309 --> 01:03:23.789
what he said.
 

01:03:23.789 --> 01:03:27.860
He did not say--many people
thought that--

01:03:27.860 --> 01:03:31.000
as previous people had often
said like Edmond Burke,

01:03:31.000 --> 01:03:32.260
who was the father of
conservatism,

01:03:32.260 --> 01:03:36.306
that the economic pie is
constant, there's just so much

01:03:36.306 --> 01:03:39.503
stuff out there,
and the more people you just

01:03:39.503 --> 01:03:42.289
have to divide the pie smaller
and smaller.

01:03:42.289 --> 01:03:44.199
That's one way of looking at it.
 

01:03:44.199 --> 01:03:47.782
Then it's perfectly obvious
that population is a bad thing

01:03:47.782 --> 01:03:51.744
because there's fixed production
and you have more people to eat

01:03:51.744 --> 01:03:53.190
up that production.
 

01:03:53.190 --> 01:03:57.673
Malthus was much smarter,
by the time he wrote in 1798

01:03:57.673 --> 01:04:01.989
the Enlightenment had started to
produce results.

01:04:01.989 --> 01:04:06.418
He could see that agricultural
production was improving year by

01:04:06.418 --> 01:04:09.034
year;
modern methods were--modern at

01:04:09.034 --> 01:04:12.840
that time--were beginning to
take over and he knew that

01:04:12.840 --> 01:04:14.179
production rose.
 

01:04:14.179 --> 01:04:17.630
What he assumed,
and what he saw from the data

01:04:17.630 --> 01:04:20.469
was that production rose
linearly,

01:04:20.469 --> 01:04:24.994
that every year there was sort
of--you could produce a little

01:04:24.994 --> 01:04:27.030
bit more out of the land.
 

01:04:27.030 --> 01:04:30.340
Now he said,
but what about population?

01:04:30.340 --> 01:04:34.804
In population if you have 100
people and they increase by

01:04:34.804 --> 01:04:39.510
let's say 50% that's 150 people,
you've gained 50 people.

01:04:39.510 --> 01:04:42.931
But now from the next
generation you again grow by

01:04:42.931 --> 01:04:46.842
50%, you're starting with 150
people you have--now you're

01:04:46.842 --> 01:04:48.309
adding 75 people.
 

01:04:48.309 --> 01:04:57.719
The graph--this is time,
this is agricultural product,

01:04:57.719 --> 01:05:05.177
and Malthus said this is
growing like this,

01:05:05.177 --> 01:05:12.989
which was quite reasonable for
his time.

01:05:12.989 --> 01:05:18.789
Population, no matter where it
starts grows--

01:05:18.789 --> 01:05:22.300
he called it geometrically,
we call it exponentially,

01:05:22.300 --> 01:05:29.268
so if it starts that there's
just enough food for people to

01:05:29.268 --> 01:05:32.990
eat,
then it almost immediately goes

01:05:32.990 --> 01:05:35.130
above food production.
 

01:05:35.130 --> 01:05:38.260
If it starts even below,
it doesn't matter;

01:05:38.260 --> 01:05:42.460
it eventually rises--catches up
with food production and goes

01:05:42.460 --> 01:05:43.300
beyond it.
 

01:05:43.300 --> 01:05:47.465
He believed that there was no
doubt that population increases

01:05:47.465 --> 01:05:50.311
geometrically,
or exponentially as we say,

01:05:50.311 --> 01:05:53.090
that means a certain percent a
year.

01:05:53.090 --> 01:05:57.840
It may increase one percent a
year or two percent a year,

01:05:57.840 --> 01:06:01.065
or three percent a year,
but remember that's one percent

01:06:01.065 --> 01:06:03.880
of an increasing number so it's
more and more.

01:06:03.880 --> 01:06:08.409
Whereas, agriculture he thought
increased linearly by the same

01:06:08.409 --> 01:06:12.268
fixed amount each year,
and if that's the case you're

01:06:12.268 --> 01:06:14.719
going to run into starvation.
 

01:06:14.719 --> 01:06:22.869
He said, since population can
always outrun productivity,

01:06:22.869 --> 01:06:26.101
eventually you get into
trouble, that whenever you

01:06:26.101 --> 01:06:30.865
increase the number of people--
if you ever--you're at some

01:06:30.865 --> 01:06:35.007
sort of stasis level,
where resources fit the

01:06:35.007 --> 01:06:36.018
population.
 

01:06:36.018 --> 01:06:40.679
But then as you get some
increase in productivity it

01:06:40.679 --> 01:06:45.250
allows a rise in population only
to match that,

01:06:45.250 --> 01:06:48.822
but then the greater number of
people eat up that increase in

01:06:48.822 --> 01:06:52.039
productivity so you're right
back down to where he--

01:06:52.039 --> 01:06:54.110
you started with.
 

01:06:54.110 --> 01:06:59.639
His idea was that increasing
population was not a good thing.

01:06:59.639 --> 01:07:04.579
It could not lead to any
improvement if it outran your

01:07:04.579 --> 01:07:08.492
productivity gains,
and this led to all kinds of

01:07:08.492 --> 01:07:11.554
what we now consider very
conservative and even

01:07:11.554 --> 01:07:13.750
retrogressive political ideas.
 

01:07:13.750 --> 01:07:17.070
So poor laws--he was initially
against poor laws.

01:07:17.070 --> 01:07:20.650
There's no sense to keep the
poor alive because if you keep

01:07:20.650 --> 01:07:24.043
them alive they're going to
reproduce and make even more

01:07:24.043 --> 01:07:27.809
children and you're right back
to where you started from.

01:07:27.809 --> 01:07:33.400
He was a strong conservative in
that sense.

01:07:33.400 --> 01:07:36.739
He later changed his mind as he
got smarter about things.

01:07:36.739 --> 01:07:40.039
He was also aware of,
even though population could

01:07:40.039 --> 01:07:42.867
increase like this,
maybe and he was aware,

01:07:42.867 --> 01:07:46.840
that people were smart enough
to stop this in some way.

01:07:46.840 --> 01:07:50.407
He knew about various methods
of contraception,

01:07:50.407 --> 01:07:54.364
withdrawal and so forth,
and various perverse sexual

01:07:54.364 --> 01:07:55.449
practices.
 

01:07:55.449 --> 01:07:58.590
But he was so opposed to them
morally,

01:07:58.590 --> 01:08:00.806
as was everyone else in his
time, that you should not

01:08:00.806 --> 01:08:02.885
control reproduction,
that that was immoral,

01:08:02.885 --> 01:08:05.239
but he said 'people are never
going to do that.'

01:08:05.239 --> 01:08:09.527
That what happens to balance it
is not people themselves

01:08:09.527 --> 01:08:12.880
controlling this in a very
rational way,

01:08:12.880 --> 01:08:15.909
which he thought was not
possible at that time,

01:08:15.909 --> 01:08:20.069
but famine would come in,
disease would come in,

01:08:20.069 --> 01:08:22.341
and whenever your population
got too big people would get

01:08:22.341 --> 01:08:22.828
very poor.
 

01:08:22.828 --> 01:08:25.840
They were open to some disease,
the disease would wipe you out.

01:08:25.840 --> 01:08:30.229
You either starved directly
immediately from too much--

01:08:30.229 --> 01:08:34.670
the population getting ahead of
agriculture productivity,

01:08:34.670 --> 01:08:38.708
you either starved or you got
to so weak that diseases come

01:08:38.708 --> 01:08:40.590
through and wipe you out.
 

